#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code stack ko recursion se reverse karta hai without using extra data structure.

1. reverseStack() function stack ka top element nikaalta hai aur baaki stack ko recursively reverse karta hai.
2. Jab recursion se wapas aate hain, to jo element nikala tha usse stack ke bottom me insert kar dete hain.
3. insertAtBottom() function recursion se bottom tak jaata hai:
   - Agar stack empty ho jaaye → element push kar do (ye bottom ban jaayega)
   - Warna top element nikaal ke recursion call karo
   - Fir wapas aate time sab elements wapas push kar do
4. Is process se har element bottom me insert hota jaata hai aur stack reverse ho jaata hai.

Main idea:
Reverse karne ka logic:
Top element nikaalo → baaki stack reverse karo → top element ko bottom me daal do.

Time Complexity: O(n^2)
Space Complexity: O(n) recursion stack

#Code:

import java.util.*;
public class Solution {
    public void reverseStack(Stack<Integer> s) {
        //You can code here
        //Base case
        if(s.isEmpty()){
          return;
        }

        int topEle = s.pop();
        reverseStack(s);
        insertAtBottom(s, topEle);     
    }

    private void insertAtBottom(Stack<Integer> s, int topEle){
      //Base case
      if(s.isEmpty()){
        s.push(topEle);
        return;
      }

      int ele = s.pop();
      insertAtBottom(s, topEle);
      s.push(ele);
    }
}
